@NODE Features "Features (Viehtschaß)"

=======================================
@{bg highlight} Features: @{bg back}
=======================================

* Works with following archive programs:

  LZX, LHA, LZH, LZ, LX, DMS, XDMS(PPCDMS), ZIP, ARC, ARJ, SIT (mit Einschränkung),
  TAR, EXE, ADF, XAD und RAR !

- you will need to install XAD for unpacking the following archives:
  CAB,CPIO,ZIP,ZOO,RAR,ARJ,BZIP,JAR,RPM,TAR,TGZ and EXE

* ExplorerNG uses now LHA2.2 to solve the LHA y2k problem!
  Please use LHA2.2 (AmiNet).

* Prefs for the location of packers/viewers/file_id...  (Since Version 4.53)
  Prefs for the language, KillDIZ, Icons, Colors,       (Since this version)
  Extensions.

* Extension Prefs Modul (with the Next Button)
  Now you can edit the internal Extensions.

* KILL DIZ
  With this you will be able to delete the file_id`s which where created with
  the Prefs-Modul "Kill DIZ" from the selected file...

* External File_ID!!!                 			(Since Version 4.53)

* ABORT function for AutoConvert !!!  			(Since Version 4.55)

* Sofort-Anzeige der File_id`s !!! siehe auch: @{" - Editor - " Link Editor}

* Archives could be repacked to LZX,LHA,TAR/TGZ,ZIP und ZOO !!!

* Repack with or wthout new pathes !!!

* "Delete File_ID" and "Delete ID`s from all files" will delete
  now hidden ID`s and files with the extension .nf0!

* Copy to archive (Working button)
  This will add an selected file to an listed archive.
  Works with lha, lzx, arc, tar/tgz, zip, zoo archives. 

* AutoRepack from whole directories to LZX!!!

* AutoRepack from whole directories to LHA!!!

* LZX-AutoRepack from whole directories with your own File_id, incl. LZX to LZX!!!

* LHA-AutoRepack from whole directories with your own File_id, incl. LZX to LHA!!!

* Create ASCII & AGuide documents from directories.

* List-Creator for File_ID`s !!! (all Packers)

* Deleting Files from Archives! (LHA, LZX, ARC, ZOO, ZIP, TAR/TGZ)

* Automatische Erkennung der Archive! -> MultiConvert

* File_id can be changed and saved to an external location !

* The new Text could be saved as File_id.diz or with a new name to the archive 
  (Jubel) siehe auch: @{"  Was ist neu in Version 3 & 4  " Link new}

* Änderungen werden sofort eingescannt !

* Auflistung des Inhalts einzelner Archive auch DMS !!!!!!!

* AmiNet .readme Texts could be saved as File_id to the archives!!!
  (complete CD directories too) (fuckin fast...)

* DMS Archiv listing will mount an virtual drive.

* File_Id (Text from Editor) could be saved to the Archive.

* ExplorerNG knows following extensions: 

  ARC, ARJ, BMP, CFG, DMS, DisplayMe, DIZ, DOC, DOK, Exe, HAM, IFF, INF, INFO, 
  JPEG (auch JPG), Gif, Guide, key, LHA, LX, LZ, LZH, LZX, MOD, nfo, PCX, Prefs,
  RAR, READ, ReadMe, SIT, TAR (auch TGZ), Tiff (auch TIF), Text, TXT, XPK, ZIP, ZOO  
  .pfb, .afm 

- and some MSDose-filetypes: 

  .bat, .sys, .exe, .dll, .mov, .avi, .386, .286, .cfg, .ico, .wav, .com, .bak
  .reg, .icl, .wri, .pif, .rsl, .hlp, .mid, .ini, .scr, .grp, .dat, .fot, .fon
  .ttl, .drv 

  and some more (at the moment 168)... (use Prefs/Extension to create more)

- The files with .GUIDE extensions could be started with an click. 

* File_id.diz can be deleted from DMS-,LZX-,LHA,TGZ/TAR,ARC,ZOO and ZIP-Archives.

* CyberShow (Picture-Viewer) Support !

* File_ID`s and other texts could be printed.

* File_Id inside of Archives could be replaced with your own File-Id. 
  (LHA,LZX,ARC,ZOO,ZIP,DMS und TAR/TGZ)

* Files/Directories could be copied, moved or just deleted!

* Makedir

* Execute Programs from ExplorerNG.

* Mount Diskdrives
  You can select the device, if you don`t want to use the df0: drive.
  You don`t need an mountlist entry for it...
  (FFx,VF0,DM0 and RAD:)
  You will need the fmsdisk,device & dms.device at DEVS:

* PPC port !!!

* Search Extension (Listen und Repack) -> GetPattern!!! 

* Mark,Cut,Copy and Paste at the Editor.

* Save a hidden file_id to the selected files.

* Geräte die über den ExplorerNG angemeldet werden, werden sofort nach Beendigung des
  Mountvorgangs in die Deviceliste eingescannt.

* Und noch einiges mehr, was ich mittlerweile vergessen habe... (Schiet, werde halt langsam alt)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Was_wird_gebraucht? "Was wird gebraucht?"

=======================================
@{fg highlight} Was wird für das Programm gebraucht?@{fg text}
=======================================

Min.:
-----

Amiga, 68020, 8MB Memory, HD

Screenmode Workbench (640*480 - 1200*1024 tested) >=256 Colors

External Screenmode tested under Picasso&CGX Software.
Only the 16Bit modis will open an new Publicscreen!

Better:
-------

68040,68060,PPC60x, more memory, more HD`s & CD drive or more CD drives
hm maybe an PeeCee???

Workbench3.x

Assign to Fonts (Total normal)
Workbench.font

The DOS commands: Copy, Delete, Rename, Search, Protect & Ed (Absolut normal)

Following Packers should be at the "C" Directory:
(You also can set a new location with the PREFS (-> Menu:User ->Prefs)!!! )

LHA, LZX, DMS, UnRAR, UnSIT, UnDMS, DMSDescript,
UnZoo, ZOO, ZIP, UnZip, EXEDescript, TAR, ARC, UnArj
XADunfile.  (Hmm, auch normal)

You will need the fmsdisk,device & dms.device at DEVS:

The Keyfile for using the buttons Guide2HTML,Save Hidden ID,DEL sel.Items,
AC DEL ID and your own File_ID...

To view pictures with the ExplorerNG you should copy CyberShow to the "C"
directory (Information for all Non-GFX-Users: CyberShow working without 
GFX-Card too). (Also tested with CyberWindow & CyberView)
You also can view pictures from archives, you only must "List" the archive!

Siehe nicht unbedingt die @{" Probleme? " Link Ochnö}

